1️⃣ What is an Expense Tracker?

An expense tracker allows users to:

Add income and expenses

Categorize spending 

View monthly/yearly summaries

See charts and analytics

Securely store personal financial data

2️⃣ Core Features 
🔐 Authentication

User signup & login

JWT-based authentication

Password hashing

💰 Expense Management

Add expense

Edit & delete expense

Add income
📊 Dashboard

Total income

Total expense

Balance

Monthly summary

🗂 Categories

Food

Transport

Rent

Shopping

Custom categories
3️⃣ Advanced Features 

Charts (Pie / Bar)

Monthly & yearly filters

Export to CSV/PDF

Dark mode

Multi-currency support

Budget limits & alerts
4️⃣ Tech Stack 
Frontend

React (with Next.js)

Tailwind CSS

Axios

Chart.js or Recharts

Backend

Node.js

Express.js

JWT Authentication
Database

MongoDB (Mongoose)

Deployment

Frontend: Vercel / Netlify

Backend: Render / Railway

Database: MongoDB Atlas
5️⃣ Full-Stack Architecture (Simple)
Frontend (Next.js)
   ↓ API Requests (Axios)
Backend (Express.js)
   ↓
Database (MongoDB)
6️⃣ Database Design (Very Important)
User Model
{
  _id,
  name,
  email,
  password,
  createdAt
}
Expense Model
{
  _id,
  userId,
  type: "income" | "expense",
  category,
  amount,
  note,
  date,
  createdAt
}
